headline: Why Kinder Morgan, Energy Transfer, and Enterprise Products Partners Rallied More Than 15% in November
summary: Pipeline companies rallied sharply in November.  Natural gas pipeline giant Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI) rallied 15.1%, according to data provided by S&P Global Market Intelligence.  Meanwhile, leading master limited partnerships (MLPs) Energy Transfer (NYSE: ET) and Enterprise Products Partners (NYSE: EPD) were both up more than 20%.
